A flow cytometry parameter defined as the midpoint value of the distribution of the areas under the orange fluorescence curve of individual particles belonging to a same cluster (or group) defined by a region.

A flow cytometry parameter defined as the midpoint value of the distribution of the areas under the red fluorescence curve of individual particles belonging to a same cluster (or group) defined by a region.

A flow cytometry parameter defined as the midpoint value of the distribution of the areas under the forward light scatter curve of individual particles belonging to a same cluster (or group) defined by a region. The Forward light scatter (FWS) corresponds to the amount of photons scattered in a frontal angle by a particle when crossing a laser beam.

A flow cytometry parameter defined as the midpoint value of the distribution of the areas under the sideward light scatter curve of individual particles belonging to a same cluster (or group) defined by a region. The Sideward light Scatter (SWS) corresponds to the amount of photons scattered at 90 degrees to the laser beam direction by a particle when crossing a laser beam.

A flow cytometry parameter defined as the sum of the areas under the green fluorescence curve of individual particles belonging to a same cluster (or group) defined by a region, divided by the number of particles in the cluster.

A flow cytometry parameter defined as the sum of the maxima (also referred to as "heights" or "peaks") of the green fluorescence curve of individual particles belonging to a same cluster (or group) defined by a region, divided by the number of particles in this very cluster.

A flow cytometry parameter defined as the sum of the areas under the orange fluorescence curve of individual particles belonging to a same cluster (or group) defined by a region, divided by the number of particles in the cluster.

A flow cytometry parameter defined as the sum of the maxima (also referred to as "heights" or "peaks") of the orange fluorescence curve of individual particles belonging to a same cluster (or group) defined by a region, divided by the number of particles in this very cluster.

A flow cytometry parameter defined as the sum of the areas under the red fluorescence curve of individual particles belonging to a same cluster (or group) defined by a region, divided by the number of particles in the cluster.

A flow cytometry parameter defined as the sum of the maxima (also referred to as "heights" or "peaks") of the red fluorescence curve of individual particles belonging to a same cluster (or group) defined by a region, divided by the number of particles in this very cluster.

A flow cytometry parameter defined as the sum of the areas under the yellow fluorescence curve of individual particles belonging to a same cluster (or group) defined by a region, divided by the number of particles in the cluster.

A flow cytometry parameter defined as the sum of the maxima (also referred to as "heights" or "peaks") of the yellow fluorescence curve of individual particles belonging to a same cluster (or group) defined by a region, divided by the number of particles in this very cluster.

A flow cytometry parameter defined as the sum of the areas under the forward light scatter curve of individual particles belonging to a same cluster (or group) defined by a region, divided by the number of particles in the cluster. The Forward light scatter (FWS) corresponds to the amount of photons scattered in a frontal angle by a particle when crossing a laser beam.

A flow cytometry parameter defined as the sum of the maxima (also referred to as "heights" or "peaks") of the forward light scatter curve of individual particles belonging to a same cluster (or group) defined by a region, divided by the number of particles in this very cluster.

A flow cytometry parameter defined as the sum of the areas under the sideward light scatter curve of individual particles belonging to a same cluster (or group) defined by a region, divided by the number of particles in the cluster. The Sideward light Scatter (SWS) corresponds to the amount of photons scattered at 90 degrees to the laser beam direction by a particle when crossing a laser beam.

A flow cytometry parameter defined as the sum of the maxima (also referred to as "heights" or "peaks") of the sideward light scatter curve of individual particles belonging to a same cluster (or group) defined by a region, divided by the number of particles in this very cluster.
